                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12834776" author="gdusbabek" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 14:35:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t understand the purpose of the while loop.  If there isn&apos;t enough space (compactionFileLocation==null), shouldn&apos;t the error be reported and the function return 0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834781" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 14:41:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the purpose is, if we can&apos;t compact all N files, see if we can compact N - 1, N - 2, etc.  Merging rows will actually free space in the average case, so it&apos;s possible that by merging some files rather than giving up completely that we will actually succeed at all of them next time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834787" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 14:48:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;better patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834789" author="gdusbabek" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 14:51:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That makes sense, but if I&apos;m reading the code correctly, the loop will always empty out smallerSSTables since compactionFileLocation is invariant.  Perhaps it should be reset in the while loop.  (Apply reset-compactionFileLocation.txt on top of your patch to see.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834803" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 15:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;definitely, +1 your fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834823" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 16:25:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;combined patch attached&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834834" author="gdusbabek" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 16:49:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834839" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 16:59:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12834878" author="hudson" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 17:54:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #357 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/357/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/357/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    use while loop instead of recursion when trimming sstables compaction list to avoid blowing stack in pathological cases.&lt;br/&gt;
patch by jbellis; reviewed by gdusbabe for &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
